President Trump delivered remarks on immigration and law enforcement at the Van Nostrand Theatre in Ronkonkoma, New York. He expressed his admiration for law enforcement officers and pledged to support them. He highlighted the threat posed by the MS-13 gang and promised to dismantle and eradicate it. The President called for increased resources for ICE officers and federal immigration judges to combat criminal gangs and secure the borders. He also reiterated his commitment to building a wall along the border with Mexico. President Trump criticized sanctuary cities and emphasized the need to enforce immigration laws to protect American communities. He concluded his remarks by thanking law enforcement officers and pledging to defend the country and put the safety of the American people first.